<% content_for(:title, "Markdown Formatting Guide") %>

<div class="markdown-demo">
  <p><strong>Markdown</strong> is a simple way of creating clean and rich text content without needing to learn a special language.</p>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <p>You can easily do simple formatting like <strong>bold</strong> and <em>italics</em>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
You can easily do simple formatting like **bold** and _italics_.
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      You can also make

      <ul>
        <li>bulleted</li>
        <li>lists</li>
        <ul>
          <li>with</li>
          <li>indented</li>
          <li>sub-lists</li>
        </ul>
      </ul>

      and

      <ol>
        <li>numbered</li>
        <li>lists</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
You can also make

* bulleted
* lists
* with
* indented
* sub-lists

and

1. numbered
2. lists
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <h1>Headers</h1>
      <h2>Are</h2>
      <h3>Easy</h3>
      <p>as well!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
# Headers
## Are
### Easy

as well!
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>You</th>
            <th>Can</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>even make pretty</td>
            <td>tables</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Wow!</td>
            <td>That's super cool!</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
| You  | Can    |
|------|--------|
| even make pretty | tables |
| Wow! | That's super cool! |
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <p>Links to external pages look <a href="http://example.com">like this</a>.</p>
      <p>Plain link text will be automatically recognized: <a href="https://gather.coop">https://gather.coop</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
Links to other pages look [like this](http://example.com).

Plain link text will be automatically recognized: https://gather.coop
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <p>You can display images like this:</p>
      <p><img src="/sample-image.png" alt="Kitty"/></p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
You can display images like this:

![Kitty](https://gather.coop/sample-image.png)
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <p>You might use a horizontal rule to divide your content:</p>
      <hr>
      <p>nice!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
You might use a horizontal rule to divide your content:

---

nice!
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="html">
      <p>If you are an advanced user and want to use raw HTML, try it out!</p>
      <p>For instance, <del>you might want to use strikethrough</del>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
      <pre>
If you are an advanced user and want to use raw HTML, try it out!

For instance, &lt;del&gt;you might want to use strikethrough&lt;/del&gt;.
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p>Now have fun creating lots of useful and beautiful content!</p>
</div>
